---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="ExpiryRP 隱私政策 / Privacy Policy" description="ExpiryRP 如何收集與使用你的資料。">

  <section class="hero" style="text-align:center;">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div style="font-size:52px; line-height:1;">🔒</div>
      <h1 style="margin-top:14px;">隱私政策 / Privacy Policy</h1>
      <span class="badge">最後更新 / Last updated：2026 年 6 月</span>
      <p class="lead" style="margin:18px auto 0;">
        本政策說明 ExpiryRP 如何收集、使用與保護你的個人資料。<br>
        This policy explains how ExpiryRP collects, uses, and protects your personal data.
      </p>
      <div class="lang-nav">
        <a href="#zh">中文</a>
        <span>·</span>
        <a href="#en">English</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 繁體中文 -->
  <section id="zh">
    <div class="wrap doc">
      <h2 class="section-title">繁體中文</h2>

      <div class="doc-card">
        <h3>1. 我們收集的資料</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>帳號資料：</strong>當你以 Google 或 Apple 登入時，我們會取得你的電子郵件、顯示名稱與頭像，用於識別你的帳號。</li>
          <li><strong>你建立的內容：</strong>物品名稱、到期日、分類、數量、備註、條碼、消耗記錄，以及你所屬的家庭群組資訊，儲存於 Firebase Firestore。</li>
          <li><strong>回報截圖：</strong>當你透過回報功能上傳截圖時，圖片儲存於 Firebase Storage。</li>
          <li><strong>物品照片：</strong>僅儲存在你的裝置本機（iOS Documents 目錄），不會上傳至任何伺服器。</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="doc-card">
        <h3>2. 我們不收集的資料</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>我們<strong>不</strong>收集廣告識別碼或追蹤用戶行為</li>
          <li>我們<strong>不</strong>將你的資料出售或提供給任何第三方廣告商</li>
          <li>我們<strong>不</strong>收集精確地理位置</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="doc-card">
        <h3>3. 資料的使用方式</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>提供物品管理、到期提醒與家庭共享等核心功能</li>
          <li>在家庭群組成員之間同步物品資料</li>
          <li>產生消耗與浪費統計</li>
          <li>發送本機通知，於物品到期前 1、3、7 天提醒你</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="doc-card">
        <h3>4. 資料儲存與第三方服務</h3>
        <p>
          本 App 使用 Google Firebase（Authentication 與 Cloud Firestore）儲存帳號與物品資料，
          受 <a href="https://firebase.google.com/support/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Firebase 隱私政策</a>規範。
          條碼商品資訊查詢使用 <a href="https://world.openfoodfacts.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Open Food Facts</a> 開放資料庫。
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="doc-card">
        <h3>5. 資料保留與刪除</h3>
        <p>你可隨時在 App 內編輯或刪除物品。若要刪除整個帳號與所有相關資料，請至官方網站 <a href="/#contact">聯絡表單</a> 提出申請，我們將在 30 天內完成處理。</p>
      </div>

      <div class="doc-card">
        <h3>6. 兒童隱私</h3>
        <p>本 App 不以 13 歲以下兒童為對象，亦不會刻意收集其個人資料。</p>
      </div>

      <div class="doc-card">
        <h3>7. 政策變更</h3>
        <p>本政策若有更新，將於本頁公布並更新上方的日期。繼續使用本 App 即表示你接受最新政策。</p>
      </div>

      <div class="doc-card">
        <h3>8. 聯絡我們</h3>
        <p>對本政策有任何疑問，請透過官方網站：<a href="/#contact">聯絡表單</a> 與我們聯繫。</p>
      </div>

      <p class="muted" style="font-size:14px; margin-top:8px;">← <a href="/expiryrp">回到 ExpiryRP</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="lang-divider" />

  <!-- English -->
  <section id="en">
    <div class="wrap doc">
      <h2 class="section-title">English</h2>

      <div class="doc-card">
        <h3>1. Data We Collect</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Account data:</strong> When you sign in with Google or Apple, we receive your email address, display name, and profile photo, used solely to identify your account.</li>
          <li><strong>Content you create:</strong> Item names, expiry dates, categories, quantities, notes, barcodes, consumption records, and household group data, stored in Firebase Firestore.</li>
          <li><strong>Feedback screenshots:</strong> When you submit feedback with a screenshot, the image is stored in Firebase Storage.</li>
          <li><strong>Item photos:</strong> Stored locally on your device only (iOS Documents directory) and never uploaded to any server.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="doc-card">
        <h3>2. Data We Do NOT Collect</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>We do <strong>not</strong> collect advertising identifiers or track user behavior</li>
          <li>We do <strong>not</strong> sell or share your data with third-party advertisers</li>
          <li>We do <strong>not</strong> collect precise geolocation</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="doc-card">
        <h3>3. How We Use Your Data</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Provide core features: item tracking, expiry reminders, and household sharing</li>
          <li>Sync item data between household members</li>
          <li>Generate consumption and waste statistics</li>
          <li>Send local notifications 1, 3, and 7 days before items expire</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="doc-card">
        <h3>4. Data Storage & Third-Party Services</h3>
        <p>
          The app uses Google Firebase (Authentication and Cloud Firestore) to store account and item data,
          governed by the <a href="https://firebase.google.com/support/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Firebase Privacy Policy</a>.
          Barcode product lookups use the <a href="https://world.openfoodfacts.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Open Food Facts</a> open database.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="doc-card">
        <h3>5. Data Retention & Deletion</h3>
        <p>You may edit or delete items at any time within the app. To delete your entire account and all associated data, please submit a request via our website <a href="/#contact">Contact Form</a>. We will process the request within 30 days.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="doc-card">
        <h3>6. Children's Privacy</h3>
        <p>This app is not directed at children under 13, and we do not knowingly collect their personal data.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="doc-card">
        <h3>7. Changes to This Policy</h3>
        <p>If this policy is updated, changes will be posted on this page with a new date. Continued use of the app constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="doc-card">
        <h3>8. Contact</h3>
        <p>For any privacy-related questions, please contact us via our website: <a href="/#contact">Contact Form</a>.</p>
      </div>

      <p class="muted" style="font-size:14px; margin-top:8px;">← <a href="/expiryrp">Back to ExpiryRP</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    .badge {
      display: inline-block; font-size: 12.5px; color: var(--muted);
      background: var(--surface-2); border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 999px; padding: 4px 14px;
    }
    .lang-nav {
      margin-top: 16px; font-size: 14px; color: var(--muted);
    }
    .lang-nav a { color: var(--text); font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none; }
    .lang-nav a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
    .lang-divider {
      border: none; border-top: 2px solid var(--border); margin: 0;
    }
    .section-title {
      font-size: 13px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: 16px;
    }
    .doc-card {
      background: var(--surface);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 16px;
      padding: 22px 24px;
      margin-bottom: 14px;
    }
    .doc-card h3 {
      font-size: 16px; text-transform: none; letter-spacing: normal;
      color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 10px;
    }
    .doc-card ul { margin-bottom: 8px; }
    .doc-card li { color: var(--muted); }
    .doc-card p { color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 1.75; }
    .doc-card strong { color: var(--text); }
  </style>
</Base>
